channel.title: Mobile phone network unblocking---- Request
channel.description:
Ok i have just bought a whole whole whole bunch of 02 sim cards (Whole meaning 200) I only paid £20.00 British sterling. I really would like to unblock my phone networck so it allows me to use various networks. When i put in one of these sim cards it says "Network blocked" "Enter your pin here" I would like to know of any "FREE" (Emphasis on the FREE) Network unblocking codes or programs etc. A program/keygen would be much much much appreciated. But i have more info if needed:
My Phone model: SGH Samsung E350E Original Network: Orange
Please do post your LEGIT files or links to crack this code =) Seriously i would be very happy.

item.title: Mobile phone network unblocking---- Request
item.dc:creator: @Rictoo Rictoo
item.description:
@Rictoo wrote:

Yeah, this is called ‘phone locking’. It actually has nothing to do with the network, it’s the phone. For some phones you can just enter a number, (eg,. #1269-21764), and it will unlock; but for some phones, you need to use a cable.

For your phone you need to…

…

…

…

…

…

…use a cable

Sorry But your phone cannot be unlocked with a code. You can get something called a ‘clip’, or just use a cable (plug into computer, then use software to unlock it). Google it to find the option you like best

Good luck! ;D
